{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":248,"text":"I have to say that I'm very glad to be here."},{"time":2651,"text":"I understand we have over 80 countries here,"},{"time":5852,"text":"so that's a whole new paradigm for me to speak"},{"time":8066,"text":"to all of these countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9445,"text":"In each country, I'm sure you have this thing called"},{"time":11430,"text":"the parent-teacher conference."},{"time":13551,"text":"Do you know about the parent-teacher conference?"},{"time":15665,"text":"Not the ones for your kids, but the one you had as a child,"},{"time":18065,"text":"where your parents come to school and your teacher"},{"time":20883,"text":"talks to your parents, and it's a little bit awkward."},{"time":23381,"text":"Well, I remember in third grade, I had this moment"},{"time":26722,"text":"where my father, who never takes off from work,"},{"time":29578,"text":"he's a classical blue collar, a working-class immigrant person,"},{"time":33508,"text":"going to school to see his son, how he's doing,"},{"time":36668,"text":"and the teacher said to him, he said, \"You know,"},{"time":39175,"text":"John is good at math and art.\""},{"time":41450,"text":"And he kind of nodded, you know?"},{"time":43512,"text":"The next day I saw him talking to a customer at our"},{"time":45882,"text":"tofu store, and he said, \"You know, John's good at math.\""},{"time":49677,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52968,"text":"And that always stuck with me all my life."},{"time":55399,"text":"Why didn't Dad say art? Why wasn't it okay?"},{"time":58256,"text":"Why? It became a question my entire life, and"},{"time":61662,"text":"that's all right, because being good at math meant"},{"time":64579,"text":"he bought me a computer, and some of you remember"},{"time":68111,"text":"this computer, this was my first computer."},{"time":69960,"text":"Who had an Apple II? Apple II users, very cool. (Applause)"},{"time":73813,"text":"As you remember, the Apple II did nothing at all. (Laughter)"},{"time":77067,"text":"You'd plug it in, you'd type in it and green text would come out."},{"time":79328,"text":"It would say you're wrong most of the time."},{"time":80885,"text":"That was the computer we knew."},{"time":82719,"text":"That computer is a computer that I learned about"},{"time":85360,"text":"going to MIT, my father's dream. And at MIT, however,"},{"time":89937,"text":"I learned about the computer at all levels,"},{"time":93183,"text":"and after, I went to art school to get away from computers,"},{"time":96863,"text":"and I began to think about the computer as more of"},{"time":99101,"text":"a spiritual space of thinking."},{"time":101282,"text":"And I was influenced by performance art --"},{"time":104136,"text":"so this is 20 years ago. I made a computer out of people."},{"time":108371,"text":"It was called the Human Powered Computer Experiment."},{"time":111409,"text":"I have a power manager, mouse driver, memory, etc.,"},{"time":115088,"text":"and I built this in Kyoto, the old capital of Japan."},{"time":118875,"text":"It's a room broken in two halves."},{"time":120840,"text":"I've turned the computer on,"},{"time":122940,"text":"and these assistants are placing a giant floppy disk"},{"time":126493,"text":"built out of cardboard, and it's put into the computer."},{"time":129339,"text":"And the floppy disk drive person wears it. (Laughter)"},{"time":133648,"text":"She finds the first sector on the disk, and"},{"time":136165,"text":"takes data off the disk and passes it off to, of course, the bus."},{"time":141496,"text":"So the bus diligently carries the data into the computer"},{"time":145052,"text":"to the memory, to the CPU, the VRAM, etc.,"},{"time":148496,"text":"and it's an actual working computer. That's a bus, really. (Laughter)"},{"time":153277,"text":"And it looks kind of fast. That's a mouse driver,"},{"time":155754,"text":"where it's XY. (Laughter)"},{"time":157753,"text":"It looks like it's happening kind of quickly, but it's actually"},{"time":159462,"text":"a very slow computer, and when I realized how slow"},{"time":162658,"text":"this computer was compared to how fast a computer is,"},{"time":166781,"text":"it made me wonder about computers and technology in general."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171418,"text":"And so I'm going to talk today about four things, really."},{"time":173543,"text":"The first three things are about how I've been curious"},{"time":177235,"text":"about technology, design and art, and how they intersect,"},{"time":180769,"text":"how they overlap, and also a topic that I've taken on"},{"time":183726,"text":"since four years ago I became the President"},{"time":185987,"text":"of Rhode Island School of Design: leadership."},{"time":189560,"text":"And I'll talk about how I've looked to combine"},{"time":192277,"text":"these four areas into a kind of a synthesis, a kind of experiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196912,"text":"So starting from technology,"},{"time":199547,"text":"technology is a wonderful thing."},{"time":201882,"text":"When that Apple II came out, it really could do nothing."},{"time":205406,"text":"It could show text and"},{"time":207876,"text":"after we waited a bit, we had these things called images."},{"time":211474,"text":"Remember when images were first possible with a computer,"},{"time":213956,"text":"those gorgeous, full-color images?"},{"time":216352,"text":"And then after a few years, we got CD-quality sound."},{"time":219570,"text":"It was incredible. You could listen to sound on the computer."},{"time":221922,"text":"And then movies, via CD-ROM. It was amazing."},{"time":225859,"text":"Remember that excitement?"},{"time":228002,"text":"And then the browser appeared. The browser was great,"},{"time":231699,"text":"but the browser was very primitive, very narrow bandwidth."},{"time":234556,"text":"Text first, then images, we waited,"},{"time":237813,"text":"CD-quality sound over the Net,"},{"time":239609,"text":"then movies over the Internet. Kind of incredible."},{"time":244253,"text":"And then the mobile phone occurred,"},{"time":247123,"text":"text, images, audio, video. And now we have iPhone,"},{"time":252658,"text":"iPad, Android, with text, video, audio, etc."},{"time":256782,"text":"You see this little pattern here?"},{"time":258809,"text":"We're kind of stuck in a loop, perhaps, and this sense"},{"time":262142,"text":"of possibility from computing is something I've been"},{"time":264748,"text":"questioning for the last 10 or so years,"},{"time":267565,"text":"and have looked to design, as we understand most things,"},{"time":271779,"text":"and to understand design with our technology has been a passion of mine."},{"time":275667,"text":"And I have a small experiment to give you a quick design lesson."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280423,"text":"Designers talk about the relationship between form"},{"time":282921,"text":"and content, content and form. Now what does that mean?"},{"time":286262,"text":"Well, content is the word up there: fear."},{"time":288829,"text":"It's a four-letter word. It's a kind of a bad feeling word, fear."},{"time":293900,"text":"Fear is set in Light Helvetica, so it's not too stressful,"},{"time":298557,"text":"and if you set it in Ultra Light Helvetica,"},{"time":301258,"text":"it's like, \"Oh, fear, who cares?\" Right? (Laughter)"},{"time":305196,"text":"You take the same Ultra Light Helvetica and make it big,"},{"time":307794,"text":"and like, whoa, that hurts. Fear."},{"time":310336,"text":"So you can see how you change the scale, you change"},{"time":312251,"text":"the form. Content is the same, but you feel differently."},{"time":316559,"text":"You change the typeface to, like, this typeface,"},{"time":318626,"text":"and it's kind of funny. It's like pirate typeface,"},{"time":321409,"text":"like Captain Jack Sparrow typeface. Arr! Fear!"},{"time":324333,"text":"Like, aww, that's not fearful. That's actually funny."},{"time":327224,"text":"Or fear like this, kind of a nightclub typeface. (Laughter)"},{"time":331093,"text":"Like, we gotta go to Fear. (Laughter)"},{"time":333513,"text":"It's, like, amazing, right? (Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":336526,"text":"It just changes the same content."},{"time":338978,"text":"Or you make it -- The letters are separated apart,"},{"time":341232,"text":"they're huddled together like on the deck of the Titanic,"},{"time":343420,"text":"and you feel sorry for the letters, like, I feel the fear."},{"time":346419,"text":"You feel for them."},{"time":348604,"text":"Or you change the typeface to something like this."},{"time":350738,"text":"It's very classy. It's like that expensive restaurant, Fear."},{"time":354270,"text":"I can never get in there. (Laughter)"},{"time":356556,"text":"It's just amazing, Fear. But that's form, content."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361842,"text":"If you just change one letter in that content,"},{"time":364891,"text":"you get a much better word, much better content: free."},{"time":368871,"text":"\"Free\" is a great word. You can serve it almost any way."},{"time":373239,"text":"Free bold feels like Mandela free."},{"time":375834,"text":"It's like, yes, I can be free."},{"time":378515,"text":"Free even light feels kind of like, ah, I can breathe in free."},{"time":381787,"text":"It feels great. Or even free spread out,"},{"time":384517,"text":"it's like, ah, I can breathe in free, so easily."},{"time":388089,"text":"And I can add in a blue gradient and a dove,"},{"time":391296,"text":"and I have, like, Don Draper free. (Laughter)"},{"time":393647,"text":"So you see that -- form, content, design, it works that way."},{"time":397009,"text":"It's a powerful thing. It's like magic, almost,"},{"time":399442,"text":"like the magicians we've seen at TED. It's magic."},{"time":403728,"text":"Design does that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406015,"text":"And I've been curious about how design and technology intersect,"},{"time":409163,"text":"and I'm going to show you some old work I never really"},{"time":410632,"text":"show anymore, to give you a sense of what I used to do."},{"time":413920,"text":"So -- yeah."},{"time":416546,"text":"So I made a lot of work in the '90s."},{"time":419737,"text":"This was a square that responds to sound."},{"time":423033,"text":"People ask me why I made that. It's not clear. (Laughter)"},{"time":426459,"text":"But I thought it'd be neat for the square"},{"time":432175,"text":"to respond to me, and my kids were small then,"},{"time":437231,"text":"and my kids would play with these things, like, \"Aaah,\""},{"time":439807,"text":"you know, they would say, \"Daddy, aaah, aaah.\" You know, like that."},{"time":442733,"text":"We'd go to a computer store, and they'd do the same thing."},{"time":445118,"text":"And they'd say, \"Daddy, why doesn't the computer respond to sound?\""},{"time":448290,"text":"And it was really at the time I was wondering why doesn't the computer respond to sound?"},{"time":451833,"text":"So I made this as a kind of an experiment at the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455052,"text":"And then I spent a lot of time in the space of"},{"time":458236,"text":"interactive graphics and things like this, and I stopped doing it because"},{"time":461205,"text":"my students at MIT got so much better than myself,"},{"time":463917,"text":"so I had to hang up my mouse."},{"time":465727,"text":"But in '96, I made my last piece. It was in black and white,"},{"time":469295,"text":"monochrome, fully monochrome, all in integer mathematics."},{"time":472522,"text":"It's called \"Tap, Type, Write.\""},{"time":474188,"text":"It's paying a tribute to the wonderful typewriter"},{"time":477674,"text":"that my mother used to type on all the time as a legal secretary."},{"time":481759,"text":"It has 10 variations. (Typing noise)"},{"time":484280,"text":"(Typing noise)"},{"time":486409,"text":"There's a shift."},{"time":489782,"text":"Ten variations. This is, like, spin the letter around."},{"time":494047,"text":"(Typing noises)"},{"time":497651,"text":"This is, like, a ring of letters. (Typing noises)"},{"time":504636,"text":"This is 20 years old, so it's kind of a --"},{"time":507547,"text":"Let's see, this is â€”"},{"time":509361,"text":"I love the French film \"The Red Balloon.\""},{"time":511477,"text":"Great movie, right? I love that movie. So,"},{"time":513735,"text":"this is sort of like a play on that. (Typing noises) (Typewriter bell)"},{"time":517343,"text":"It's peaceful, like that. (Laughter)"},{"time":521473,"text":"I'll show this last one. This is about balance, you know."},{"time":525640,"text":"It's kind of stressful typing out, so if you"},{"time":527591,"text":"type on this keyboard, you can, like, balance it out."},{"time":530952,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":533022,"text":"If you hit G, life's okay, so I always say,"},{"time":535570,"text":"\"Hit G, and it's going to be all right."},{"time":538927,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":541438,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544085,"text":"So that was 20 years ago, and"},{"time":547417,"text":"I was always on the periphery of art."},{"time":552059,"text":"By being President of RISD I've gone deep into art,"},{"time":554409,"text":"and art is a wonderful thing, fine art, pure art."},{"time":558068,"text":"You know, when people say, \"I don't get art."},{"time":560872,"text":"I don't get it at all.\" That means art is working, you know?"},{"time":565260,"text":"It's like, art is supposed to be enigmatic, so when you say,"},{"time":567336,"text":"like, \"I don't get it,\" like, oh, that's great. (Laughter)"},{"time":570300,"text":"Art does that, because art is about asking questions,"},{"time":572932,"text":"questions that may not be answerable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575644,"text":"At RISD, we have this amazing facility called"},{"time":577572,"text":"the Edna Lawrence Nature Lab. It has 80,000 samples"},{"time":581242,"text":"of animal, bone, mineral, plants."},{"time":584823,"text":"You know, in Rhode Island, if an animal gets hit on the road,"},{"time":587533,"text":"they call us up and we pick it up and stuff it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590707,"text":"And why do we have this facility?"},{"time":593248,"text":"Because at RISD, you have to look at the actual animal,"},{"time":596691,"text":"the object, to understand its volume, to perceive it."},{"time":599571,"text":"At RISD, you're not allowed to draw from an image."},{"time":602283,"text":"And many people ask me, John, couldn't you just"},{"time":603948,"text":"digitize all this? Make it all digital? Wouldn't it be better?"},{"time":608076,"text":"And I often say, well, there's something good to how things"},{"time":611018,"text":"used to be done. There's something very different about it,"},{"time":614683,"text":"something we should figure out what is good about"},{"time":617009,"text":"how we did it, even in this new era."},{"time":620086,"text":"And I have a good friend, he's a new media artist named"},{"time":622977,"text":"Tota Hasegawa. He's based in London, no, actually it's in Tokyo,"},{"time":626515,"text":"but when he was based in London, he had a game"},{"time":628617,"text":"with his wife. He would go to antique shops,"},{"time":631908,"text":"and the game was as such:"},{"time":634055,"text":"When we look at an antique we want,"},{"time":636736,"text":"we'll ask the shopkeeper for the story behind the antique,"},{"time":639583,"text":"and if it's a good story, we'll buy it."},{"time":641213,"text":"So they'd go to an antique shop, and they'd look at this cup,"},{"time":643454,"text":"and they'd say, \"Tell us about this cup.\""},{"time":644783,"text":"And the shopkeeper would say, \"It's old.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":648887,"text":"\"Tell us more.\"\n\"Oh, it's really old.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":652611,"text":"And he saw, over and over, the antique's value"},{"time":655157,"text":"was all about it being old."},{"time":657820,"text":"And as a new media artist, he reflected, and said,"},{"time":660329,"text":"you know, I've spent my whole career making new media art."},{"time":662973,"text":"People say, \"Wow, your art, what is it?\"\nIt's new media."},{"time":667675,"text":"And he realized, it isn't about old or new."},{"time":670713,"text":"It's about something in between."},{"time":672227,"text":"It isn't about \"old,\" the dirt, \"new,\" the cloud. It's about what is good."},{"time":677688,"text":"A combination of the cloud and the dirt is where the action is at."},{"time":683122,"text":"You see it in all interesting art today, in all"},{"time":685106,"text":"interesting businesses today. How we combine"},{"time":687125,"text":"those two together to make good is very interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691414,"text":"So art makes questions, and"},{"time":694185,"text":"leadership is something that is asking a lot of questions."},{"time":699008,"text":"We aren't functioning so easily anymore."},{"time":701010,"text":"We aren't a simple authoritarian regime anymore."},{"time":704138,"text":"As an example of authoritarianism, I was in Russia one time"},{"time":707544,"text":"traveling in St. Petersburg, at a national monument,"},{"time":709720,"text":"and I saw this sign that says, \"Do Not Walk On The Grass,\""},{"time":712882,"text":"and I thought, oh, I mean, I speak English,"},{"time":714525,"text":"and you're trying to single me out. That's not fair."},{"time":717262,"text":"But I found a sign for Russian-speaking people,"},{"time":720136,"text":"and it was the best sign ever to say no."},{"time":723309,"text":"It was like, \"No swimming, no hiking, no anything.\""},{"time":726033,"text":"My favorite ones are \"no plants.\" Why would you bring a plant to a national monument? I'm not sure."},{"time":731632,"text":"And also \"no love.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":733905,"text":"So that is authoritarianism."},{"time":737458,"text":"And what is that, structurally?"},{"time":739623,"text":"It's a hierarchy. We all know that a hierarchy is how we run"},{"time":742373,"text":"many systems today, but as we know, it's been disrupted."},{"time":745398,"text":"It is now a network instead of a perfect tree."},{"time":748916,"text":"It's a heterarchy instead of a hierarchy. And that's kind of awkward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752136,"text":"And so today, leaders are faced"},{"time":755536,"text":"with how to lead differently, I believe."},{"time":757450,"text":"This is work I did with my colleague Becky Bermont"},{"time":759680,"text":"on creative leadership. What can we learn"},{"time":761920,"text":"from artists and designers for how to lead?"},{"time":764345,"text":"Because in many senses, a regular leader loves to avoid mistakes."},{"time":768350,"text":"Someone who's creative actually loves to learn from mistakes."},{"time":772423,"text":"A traditional leader is always wanting to be right,"},{"time":775601,"text":"whereas a creative leader hopes to be right."},{"time":780062,"text":"And this frame is important today, in this complex,"},{"time":782560,"text":"ambiguous space, and artists and designers have a lot to teach us, I believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787330,"text":"And I had a show in London recently where my friends"},{"time":791040,"text":"invited me to come to London for four days"},{"time":792917,"text":"to sit in a sandbox, and I said great."},{"time":795379,"text":"And so I sat in a sandbox for four days straight,"},{"time":798727,"text":"six hours every day, six-minute appointments with anyone in London,"},{"time":801888,"text":"and that was really bad."},{"time":804075,"text":"But I would listen to people, hear their issues,"},{"time":807707,"text":"draw in the sand, try to figure things out,"},{"time":809601,"text":"and it was kind of hard to figure out what I was doing."},{"time":812144,"text":"You know? It's all these one-on-one meetings for like four days."},{"time":814852,"text":"And it felt kind of like being president, actually."},{"time":816758,"text":"I was like, \"Oh, this my job. President. I do a lot of meetings, you know?\""},{"time":819755,"text":"And by the end of the experience,"},{"time":821663,"text":"I realized why I was doing this."},{"time":824502,"text":"It's because leaders, what we do is we connect"},{"time":828631,"text":"improbable connections and hope something will happen,"},{"time":832788,"text":"and in that room I found so many connections"},{"time":834543,"text":"between people across all of London, and so leadership,"},{"time":838863,"text":"connecting people, is the great question today."},{"time":841500,"text":"Whether you're in the hierarchy or the heterarchy,"},{"time":843757,"text":"it's a wonderful design challenge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846152,"text":"And one thing I've been doing is doing some research"},{"time":849877,"text":"on systems that can combine technology and leadership"},{"time":853525,"text":"with an art and design perspective."},{"time":854519,"text":"Let me show you something I haven't shown anywhere, actually."},{"time":858792,"text":"So what this is, is a kind of a sketch, an application sketch"},{"time":861234,"text":"I wrote in Python. You know how there's Photoshop?"},{"time":863792,"text":"This is called Powershop, and the way it works is"},{"time":868051,"text":"imagine an organization. You know, the CEO isn't ever"},{"time":871078,"text":"at the top. The CEO's at the center of the organization."},{"time":873360,"text":"There may be different subdivisions in the organization,"},{"time":875579,"text":"and you might want to look into different areas. For instance,"},{"time":878264,"text":"green are areas doing well, red are areas doing poorly."},{"time":881766,"text":"You know, how do you, as the leader, scan, connect,"},{"time":884016,"text":"make things happen? So for instance, you might open up"},{"time":887020,"text":"a distribution here and find the different subdivisions in there,"},{"time":890170,"text":"and know that you know someone in Eco, over here,"},{"time":893881,"text":"and"},{"time":895862,"text":"these people here are in Eco, the people you might"},{"time":897870,"text":"engage with as CEO, people going across the hierarchy."},{"time":901938,"text":"And part of the challenge of the CEO is to find"},{"time":905023,"text":"connections across areas, and so you might look in R&amp;D,"},{"time":908482,"text":"and here you see one person who crosses the two areas"},{"time":911682,"text":"of interest, and it's a person important to engage."},{"time":915239,"text":"So you might want to, for instance, get a heads-up display"},{"time":919275,"text":"on how you're interacting with them."},{"time":921874,"text":"How many coffees do you have?"},{"time":923453,"text":"How often are you calling them, emailing them?"},{"time":926847,"text":"What is the tenor of their email? How is it working out?"},{"time":929637,"text":"Leaders might be able to use these systems to"},{"time":931999,"text":"better regulate how they work inside the heterarchy."},{"time":934981,"text":"You can also imagine using technology like from Luminoso,"},{"time":938408,"text":"the guys from Cambridge who were looking at deep"},{"time":940933,"text":"text analysis. What is the tenor of your communications?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":944162,"text":"So these kind of systems, I believe, are important."},{"time":947615,"text":"They're targeted social media systems around leaders."},{"time":950473,"text":"And I believe that this kind of perspective will only begin"},{"time":953782,"text":"to grow as more leaders enter the space of art and design,"},{"time":959089,"text":"because art and design lets you think like this,"},{"time":962514,"text":"find different systems like this,"},{"time":964289,"text":"and I've just begun thinking like this,"},{"time":966162,"text":"so I'm glad to share that with you."},{"time":968095,"text":"So in closing, I want to thank all of you"},{"time":971277,"text":"for your attention. Thanks very much. (Applause)"},{"time":975359,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}